13/02/2004
PARIS, France -- Romanian gendarmes are participating in a partnership training forum with the European Police Force in France late this week, with an emphasis on managing post-crisis public disorder.
The meeting will propose scenarios for several training exercises in June.
Romania will send 30 officers.
The programme was drafted in co-operation with the French National Gendarmerie and the Spanish Civil Guard.
(Rompres - 13/02/04)
